1
00:00:18,960 --> 00:00:20,800
The Young Master
went on a date today.

2
00:00:22,680 --> 00:00:23,640
With who?

3
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:25,520
A man.

4
00:00:25,800 --> 00:00:27,080
A man?

5
00:00:27,280 --> 00:00:28,200
And a woman.

6
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:30,040
They're Zhao Chengru's son and daughter.

7
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:32,720
=Cases Between Us=

8
00:00:32,720 --> 00:00:33,960
Can you finish the sentence

9
00:00:33,960 --> 00:00:36,640
before you pause?

10
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:37,520
Yes, sir.

11
00:00:37,520 --> 00:00:38,900
=Episode 9=

12
00:00:39,560 --> 00:00:42,880
Isn't his daughter Wu Shichuan's wife?

13
00:00:42,880 --> 00:00:43,320
She was.

14
00:00:43,960 --> 00:00:45,880
Wu Shichuan died in prison not long ago.

15
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:46,840
They had divorced

16
00:00:47,000 --> 00:00:48,000
before he died.

17
00:00:50,440 --> 00:00:51,480
A date?

18
00:00:53,953 --> 00:00:56,840
How can you be so sure it was a date?

19
00:00:56,880 --> 00:00:59,350
They went to Young Master's
least favorite Western restaurant.

20
00:00:59,360 --> 00:01:01,310
They even ordered a bottle
of wine and finished it.

21
00:01:01,320 --> 00:01:04,120
During dinner, Young Master
gave Young Lady Zhao a pistol.

22
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:06,080
She seemed to like it very much.

23
00:01:06,080 --> 00:01:07,080
What about Zhao's son?

24
00:01:07,320 --> 00:01:09,240
They solved
the child kidnapping case together.

25
00:01:09,240 --> 00:01:12,080
Tonight, they went to Young Master's
courtyard and had noodles together.

26
00:01:12,112 --> 00:01:13,580
Also, Young Master Zhao got a newspaper

27
00:01:13,590 --> 00:01:15,090
to publish a special edition
about himself.

28
00:01:15,104 --> 00:01:15,984
It comes out tomorrow.

29
00:01:16,560 --> 00:01:18,520
It doesn't mention Young Master
in the case at all.

30
00:01:19,440 --> 00:01:20,640
Not a single word?

31
00:01:21,960 --> 00:01:25,280
He's just trying to

32
00:01:25,280 --> 00:01:27,000
steal Hong's thunder.

33
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:29,840
Buy every copy.

34
00:01:29,840 --> 00:01:31,440
Don't let a single one reach the public.

35
00:01:31,440 --> 00:01:32,200
Understood?

36
00:01:32,200 --> 00:01:32,680
Yes, sir.

37
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:40,160
Anything else?

38
00:01:42,120 --> 00:01:45,160
The Cabinet has become very unhappy
with Young Master lately.

39
00:01:47,680 --> 00:01:50,400
The Cabinet is unhappy with him?

40
00:01:51,600 --> 00:01:52,640
They're nothing more

41
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:54,920
than a bunch of paper-pushers.

42
00:01:57,840 --> 00:01:59,200
If they're upset,

43
00:02:01,080 --> 00:02:02,680
they can keep it to themselves.

44
00:02:03,880 --> 00:02:05,480
If they're angry,

45
00:02:06,680 --> 00:02:08,560
they'd better swallow it.

46
00:02:09,664 --> 00:02:11,400
I'm afraid they won't be able to
much longer.

47
00:02:11,480 --> 00:02:12,400
What do you mean?

48
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:14,550
The pharmaceutical company
and the tram company

49
00:02:14,560 --> 00:02:16,496
that they invested in
have both taken heavy losses.

50
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:18,560
The Cabinet is now
full of General Chen's people.

51
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:20,680
Which means

52
00:02:21,088 --> 00:02:23,160
it's General Chen's money
that's gone up in smoke.

53
00:02:23,400 --> 00:02:24,880
And the word outside is

54
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:27,760
that you were the one
who told Young Master to do all this.

55
00:02:30,680 --> 00:02:33,080
Only if Hong

56
00:02:33,320 --> 00:02:34,480
had listened to me.

57
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:38,200
I only wish

58
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:41,920
he'd think about the bigger picture.

59
00:02:42,520 --> 00:02:45,480
Anything's better
than chasing petty crime

60
00:02:45,480 --> 00:02:47,880
at that police department.

61
00:02:48,640 --> 00:02:50,760
What a waste of time.

62
00:03:51,080 --> 00:03:51,800
Young Master.

63
00:03:52,560 --> 00:03:53,200
Young Master.

64
00:03:54,288 --> 00:03:55,320
Where's the newspaper?

65
00:03:55,408 --> 00:03:56,336
Couldn't get one.

66
00:03:56,352 --> 00:03:58,448
I went to the newsstand
across the street this morning.

67
00:03:58,464 --> 00:03:59,520
There wasn't a single copy.

68
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:01,080
Then I called Lei

69
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,760
and had him check the stands
in South City.

70
00:04:02,760 --> 00:04:04,040
He asked around,

71
00:04:04,040 --> 00:04:06,040
and they said every copy had sold out

72
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:07,160
the moment it hit the shelves.

73
00:04:07,160 --> 00:04:08,120
Not one was left.

74
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:21,000
Father.

75
00:04:21,480 --> 00:04:22,240
Morning, Master.

76
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:24,480
Where's Shaoshang?

77
00:04:25,960 --> 00:04:26,760
Not home.

78
00:04:27,520 --> 00:04:29,200
He's been busy with cases lately.

79
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,040
He's always out.

80
00:04:30,360 --> 00:04:32,360
Looks like he's serious
about becoming a cop.

81
00:04:33,280 --> 00:04:35,960
It'd be nice if he really meant it.

82
00:04:35,960 --> 00:04:37,880
I'm just worried

83
00:04:38,200 --> 00:04:39,600
it's only a passing fancy.

84
00:04:40,368 --> 00:04:42,360
The other day, he said
he wanted to be a reporter,

85
00:04:42,360 --> 00:04:44,112
so I pulled some strings
to get him the job.

86
00:04:44,128 --> 00:04:46,000
A few days later,
he said he wanted to quit.

87
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,856
I had to apologize
to the people who helped him.

88
00:04:48,040 --> 00:04:48,480
Father.

89
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:49,440
Which newspaper was it?

90
00:04:49,880 --> 00:04:50,640
Ta Kung Pao.

91
00:04:51,080 --> 00:04:51,760
The chief editor

92
00:04:51,760 --> 00:04:53,360
is an old friend of mine.

93
00:04:55,040 --> 00:04:56,080
Do they hire women?

94
00:04:59,720 --> 00:05:00,640
I'd like to try.

95
00:05:00,880 --> 00:05:01,840
I want to be a reporter.

96
00:05:01,904 --> 00:05:03,000
I want to speak up for women

97
00:05:03,000 --> 00:05:04,820
and fight for their rights
through the press.

98
00:05:07,080 --> 00:05:08,600
Being a reporter is hard work.

99
00:05:08,640 --> 00:05:10,368
I'm not afraid of hard work, Mother.

100
00:05:10,800 --> 00:05:12,240
I'm afraid of being bored.

101
00:05:13,600 --> 00:05:15,080
I'm almost thirty.

102
00:05:15,520 --> 00:05:17,400
But I live like I'm eighty.

103
00:05:18,560 --> 00:05:19,760
If I don't do something now,

104
00:05:19,760 --> 00:05:21,360
I'll be completely left behind.

105
00:05:28,160 --> 00:05:29,120
Father.

106
00:05:29,680 --> 00:05:30,360
Mother.

107
00:05:35,720 --> 00:05:36,320
Alright.

108
00:05:36,480 --> 00:05:38,480
I'll make a call tonight.

109
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:40,480
Hopefully, you can start tomorrow.

110
00:05:40,480 --> 00:05:41,860
Thank you, Father. Don't worry.

111
00:05:41,872 --> 00:05:43,400
I won't disgrace the Zhao family.

112
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:45,360
I know.

113
00:05:45,960 --> 00:05:46,920
I'm not worried at all.

114
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:47,880
Now eat.

115
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:55,480
Why was Director Zheng released?

116
00:05:59,440 --> 00:06:00,640
When you get down to it,

117
00:06:00,880 --> 00:06:02,200
this whole thing

118
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:04,000
was caused by the Ministry of Transport

119
00:06:04,000 --> 00:06:05,560
putting too much pressure on him.

120
00:06:05,800 --> 00:06:07,200
Besides, Director Zheng

121
00:06:07,440 --> 00:06:08,760
isn't a bad man.

122
00:06:09,040 --> 00:06:10,640
He just went too far.

123
00:06:11,120 --> 00:06:12,080
But he only did it

124
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:14,560
to push Beijing's development forward.

125
00:06:14,560 --> 00:06:15,960
Then what am I solving cases for?

126
00:06:17,560 --> 00:06:19,320
The injured child

127
00:06:19,320 --> 00:06:20,680
was his own grandson.

128
00:06:20,680 --> 00:06:21,500
Besides,

129
00:06:21,500 --> 00:06:22,960
it didn't cause

130
00:06:22,960 --> 00:06:24,930
- any major public impact.
- How is that...

131
00:06:26,360 --> 00:06:26,920
That's enough.

132
00:06:27,240 --> 00:06:27,880
We're done here.

133
00:06:30,040 --> 00:06:30,720
You may leave.

134
00:06:31,960 --> 00:06:32,480
Hello?

135
00:06:33,480 --> 00:06:34,160
Secretary Xu.

136
00:06:36,000 --> 00:06:36,600
Yes?

137
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:41,320
Chief Yuan.

138
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:08,120
Who'd dare

139
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,640
make a fool of you?

140
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:10,680
They must have a death wish.

141
00:07:11,424 --> 00:07:12,880
Did I do something to offend you?

142
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:14,520
We get along just fine.

143
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:16,600
Why are you saying that?

144
00:07:16,600 --> 00:07:17,560
Or is your guilty

145
00:07:18,520 --> 00:07:19,680
conscience bothering you?

146
00:07:20,600 --> 00:07:22,160
What have I got to feel guilty about?

147
00:07:22,160 --> 00:07:23,600
You know what you've done.

148
00:07:23,880 --> 00:07:24,720
One word.

149
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:25,680
Dirty.

150
00:07:26,280 --> 00:07:27,600
Say that again. Who's dirty?

151
00:07:27,600 --> 00:07:28,240
What?

152
00:07:28,288 --> 00:07:29,120
Trying to scare me?

153
00:07:29,120 --> 00:07:29,800
I'm timid.

154
00:07:30,912 --> 00:07:32,920
This is the police department,
not your house.

155
00:07:33,008 --> 00:07:34,704
You don't get to do whatever you want.

156
00:07:35,920 --> 00:07:36,840
Someone!

157
00:07:37,104 --> 00:07:38,160
The police are beating me!

158
00:07:38,160 --> 00:07:39,080
Someone!

159
00:07:39,080 --> 00:07:40,040
Come over!

160
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:41,160
Look at him.

161
00:07:41,216 --> 00:07:42,930
(Jingshi Police Department)
Come take a look!

162
00:07:43,808 --> 00:07:45,712
Don't just stand there watching.
Help me out!

163
00:07:45,712 --> 00:07:46,976
Have you people no compassion?

164
00:07:47,600 --> 00:07:49,840
If you've got a problem with me,
just say it.

165
00:07:50,240 --> 00:07:51,600
Stop pulling these petty tricks

166
00:07:51,600 --> 00:07:52,920
like a child.

167
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:53,760
It's immature.

168
00:07:55,424 --> 00:07:57,160
You bought up
all those special editions?

169
00:07:57,160 --> 00:07:59,168
You even have room to
store that many newspapers?

170
00:07:59,904 --> 00:08:00,920
What special edition?

171
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:02,160
Still pretending?

172
00:08:02,496 --> 00:08:04,128
You did it, but you won't admit it.

173
00:08:06,080 --> 00:08:06,960
Explain yourself.

174
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:14,770
I'm only at the police department
to build my reputation.

175
00:08:14,784 --> 00:08:15,680
I need to become famous

176
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:17,000
so I can climb the ranks quickly.

177
00:08:17,160 --> 00:08:18,400
Every case we work together on,

178
00:08:18,448 --> 00:08:19,936
I'll be the one getting all the credit.

179
00:08:19,968 --> 00:08:20,800
So, Young Master Zhao,

180
00:08:20,800 --> 00:08:22,304
you'd better keep your distance from me.

181
00:08:27,600 --> 00:08:28,400
I must've been blind

182
00:08:28,400 --> 00:08:29,680
to work with a scoundrel like you.

183
00:08:35,680 --> 00:08:37,240
Young Master Lu.

184
00:08:37,240 --> 00:08:39,200
Don't be angry, Young Master Lu.

185
00:08:39,440 --> 00:08:40,816
Young Master Lu.

186
00:08:40,820 --> 00:08:42,320
(Handan Pleasure House)
Don't be angry.

187
00:08:42,320 --> 00:08:43,440
(Lu Ruiheng)
It's my fault.

188
00:08:43,520 --> 00:08:44,440
Don't be mad, please.

189
00:08:44,800 --> 00:08:45,160
Alright.

190
00:08:45,160 --> 00:08:45,960
Don't drink too much.

191
00:08:45,960 --> 00:08:46,850
(Xiaoman)
Young Master Lu.

192
00:08:46,860 --> 00:08:48,870
(Madam Feng)
I haven't disciplined my girls well.

193
00:08:48,880 --> 00:08:49,744
Please don't be angry.

194
00:08:56,080 --> 00:08:57,200
What a spoilsport.

195
00:08:57,200 --> 00:08:57,840
Young Master Lu.

196
00:08:57,840 --> 00:08:58,800
Alright, Young Master Lu.

197
00:08:59,000 --> 00:08:59,640
Go back.

198
00:08:59,640 --> 00:09:00,400
Rickshaw!

199
00:09:00,540 --> 00:09:01,400
(Handan Pleasure House)

200
00:09:01,400 --> 00:09:02,440
Take care, Young Master Lu.

201
00:09:02,440 --> 00:09:03,760
Don't be mad. Bad for your health.

202
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:05,680
It's fine. Watch your step.
Broken glass. Easy.

203
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:06,280
Take care.

204
00:09:06,280 --> 00:09:07,040
Don't be angry.

205
00:09:07,520 --> 00:09:08,520
- Go.
- Take care.

206
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:09,800
Take care, Young Master Lu.

207
00:09:09,800 --> 00:09:10,800
It's all my fault.

208
00:09:10,800 --> 00:09:11,520
Young Master Lu.

209
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:13,280
Come back.

210
00:09:18,480 --> 00:09:19,360
You still kept

211
00:09:19,680 --> 00:09:20,520
the hair oil?

212
00:09:22,592 --> 00:09:23,840
It's good stuff. Would've been

213
00:09:23,880 --> 00:09:25,600
(Mulian Hair Oil)
a waste to throw it away.

214
00:09:27,840 --> 00:09:30,240
He saw Qiao'er hang herself
with his own eyes.

215
00:09:30,760 --> 00:09:31,800
Surely the smell

216
00:09:31,800 --> 00:09:32,960
would haunt him.

217
00:09:34,360 --> 00:09:35,920
You even kept a dead person's thing.

218
00:09:38,120 --> 00:09:38,960
Fine.

219
00:09:39,280 --> 00:09:40,840
I'm done entertaining that Lu fellow.

220
00:09:40,840 --> 00:09:42,544
Not even the tonic could make him do it.

221
00:09:43,080 --> 00:09:43,880
Clean up

222
00:09:43,880 --> 00:09:44,840
the broken glass.

223
00:09:44,840 --> 00:09:45,320
Hurry up.

224
00:09:52,420 --> 00:09:55,420
(Mulian Hair Oil)

225
00:10:04,560 --> 00:10:05,040
Mister.

226
00:10:10,660 --> 00:10:13,400
(Shengxiamei Hair Salon)

227
00:10:13,400 --> 00:10:14,960
Didn't I tell you
to take me to Nanchizi?

228
00:10:15,240 --> 00:10:16,160
Where is this?

229
00:10:16,520 --> 00:10:17,680
Do you even know the way?

230
00:10:17,680 --> 00:10:18,320
Mister,

231
00:10:18,640 --> 00:10:20,480
a beautiful young lady paid the fare

232
00:10:20,760 --> 00:10:22,320
and told me I had to bring you here.

233
00:10:22,600 --> 00:10:23,720
A beautiful young lady?

234
00:10:25,840 --> 00:10:26,880
What's her name?

235
00:10:27,360 --> 00:10:28,640
That's your romantic mess.

236
00:10:28,880 --> 00:10:30,200
Why are you asking me?

237
00:10:30,320 --> 00:10:30,840
You rascal!

238
00:10:30,840 --> 00:10:31,760
Say that again.

239
00:10:32,000 --> 00:10:33,080
Making fun of me, are you?

240
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:39,160
Don't leave!

241
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:41,080
Take me with you!

242
00:10:45,680 --> 00:10:46,480
Lu Ruiheng.

243
00:10:49,800 --> 00:10:50,600
Lu Ruiheng.

244
00:10:52,800 --> 00:10:53,720
Qiao'er?

245
00:11:20,300 --> 00:11:23,580
(Mulian Hair Oil)

246
00:11:26,320 --> 00:11:28,080
Mulian hair oil...

247
00:11:40,480 --> 00:11:41,480
Murder!

248
00:11:41,480 --> 00:11:43,340
(South City)

249
00:11:49,660 --> 00:11:54,980
(No Entry)

250
00:12:03,760 --> 00:12:04,440
Thank you.

251
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:07,240
A murder case?

252
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:08,800
Young Lady Zhao,

253
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:10,880
what brings you here?

254
00:12:10,976 --> 00:12:12,120
I'm here to report on it.

255
00:12:13,520 --> 00:12:14,520
You're journalist now?

256
00:12:15,008 --> 00:12:16,240
(Press Pass)
Ta Kung Pao.

257
00:12:16,240 --> 00:12:17,480
Today's my first day.

258
00:12:19,560 --> 00:12:20,640
Sorry,

259
00:12:20,640 --> 00:12:23,000
no interviews
while we're processing a crime scene.

260
00:12:23,400 --> 00:12:24,880
I wasn't here to interview you.

261
00:12:24,880 --> 00:12:25,680
No one gets in.

262
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:27,400
This is a crime scene.

263
00:12:27,400 --> 00:12:28,440
Anyone not involved,

264
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:29,400
please leave.

265
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:30,760
Bye.

266
00:12:35,580 --> 00:12:38,340
(Shengxiamei Hair Salon)

267
00:12:44,920 --> 00:12:45,760
Sorry.

268
00:12:46,200 --> 00:12:47,440
We're closed today.

269
00:12:48,400 --> 00:12:49,880
I read in a magazine

270
00:12:49,880 --> 00:12:51,560
that a perm here costs six silver coins.

271
00:12:51,760 --> 00:12:52,600
Look outside.

272
00:12:52,752 --> 00:12:54,240
The place is crawling with police.

273
00:12:57,880 --> 00:12:58,840
I'll pay fifty.

274
00:12:59,024 --> 00:13:00,512
Is it enough to book the whole salon?

275
00:13:01,980 --> 00:13:05,660
(Xia Jinshu,
Owner of Shengxiamei Hair Salon)

276
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:09,120
Let's start with a shampoo.

277
00:13:14,800 --> 00:13:15,480
Chief,

278
00:13:15,504 --> 00:13:17,280
why hasn't Young Master Zhao
shown up today?

279
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:23,120
Look.

280
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:25,200
You didn't buy up
those special editions.

281
00:13:25,360 --> 00:13:26,160
If he misunderstood,

282
00:13:26,160 --> 00:13:27,440
why not just explain it?

283
00:13:27,440 --> 00:13:29,600
If you're free, I'll find
someone else to do your job.

284
00:13:31,240 --> 00:13:32,304
I'll keep my mouth shut.

285
00:13:32,960 --> 00:13:33,360
Careful.

286
00:13:37,360 --> 00:13:38,200
How is it?

287
00:13:38,200 --> 00:13:38,960
Happy with it?

288
00:13:40,880 --> 00:13:41,400
It's done.

289
00:13:48,440 --> 00:13:49,120
Thank you.

290
00:13:49,680 --> 00:13:50,280
My pleasure.

291
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:55,200
Ms. Xia.

292
00:13:57,616 --> 00:13:59,904
You used to work
at Handan Pleasure House, didn't you?

293
00:14:03,960 --> 00:14:05,600
I'm a reporter with Ta Kung Pao.

294
00:14:05,744 --> 00:14:07,664
(Press Pass)
I'd like to do a feature on you.

295
00:14:11,480 --> 00:14:12,400
I don't think

296
00:14:13,200 --> 00:14:14,280
we should do that.

297
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:17,000
I truly think

298
00:14:17,000 --> 00:14:18,320
you're strong and independent.

299
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:20,040
You changed your life

300
00:14:20,040 --> 00:14:21,520
with your own skills.

301
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:23,560
You're a role model for women today.

302
00:14:24,320 --> 00:14:25,120
A role model?

303
00:14:26,680 --> 00:14:28,360
You want to use my private life

304
00:14:28,360 --> 00:14:30,280
to satisfy your readers' curiosity

305
00:14:30,600 --> 00:14:32,160
and sell more newspapers.

306
00:14:32,680 --> 00:14:33,840
Do you call that a virtue?

307
00:14:34,040 --> 00:14:34,520
No.

308
00:14:34,520 --> 00:14:36,040
Please believe me.

309
00:14:36,040 --> 00:14:38,120
I truly admire you.

310
00:14:40,400 --> 00:14:40,840
Fine.

311
00:14:41,480 --> 00:14:43,160
If you really want to understand me,

312
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,440
then try

313
00:14:44,440 --> 00:14:45,600
living my life first.

314
00:14:46,160 --> 00:14:48,944
Go over to the Eight Alleys.
[*Beijing's famous red-light district]

315
00:14:49,400 --> 00:14:51,600
Eat and drink with customers.

316
00:14:52,680 --> 00:14:54,080
With your looks,

317
00:14:54,280 --> 00:14:57,400
you may not become the top girl,
but you'll make a living.

318
00:14:58,040 --> 00:14:59,960
I'll introduce you to some clients.

319
00:15:00,520 --> 00:15:02,160
If you make money,

320
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:03,560
give me a cut.

321
00:15:03,960 --> 00:15:05,080
I'm not greedy.

322
00:15:05,680 --> 00:15:06,600
One-tenth is enough.

323
00:15:08,080 --> 00:15:09,480
You're just trying to provoke me

324
00:15:09,480 --> 00:15:10,600
to refuse the interview.

325
00:15:12,720 --> 00:15:14,560
Girls like you, from wealthy families,

326
00:15:15,360 --> 00:15:17,560
can get a job as easily
as eating a meal.

327
00:15:17,800 --> 00:15:19,200
You've never had to worry

328
00:15:19,200 --> 00:15:20,400
about survival.

329
00:15:21,040 --> 00:15:23,600
So don't pretend to be kind

330
00:15:23,600 --> 00:15:24,440
or compassionate.

331
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:26,480
You'll never understand

332
00:15:27,720 --> 00:15:29,240
what we've been through.

333
00:15:29,920 --> 00:15:30,320
I...

334
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:30,960
Sorry.

335
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:33,200
We're closed for the day.

336
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:01,880
I knew it.

337
00:16:02,280 --> 00:16:04,080
You never stick with anything.

338
00:16:05,560 --> 00:16:06,200
Father,

339
00:16:07,800 --> 00:16:09,200
it wasn't my fault this time.

340
00:16:09,200 --> 00:16:11,320
He's the one who stabbed me in the back.

341
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:13,560
What did he do?

342
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:15,720
Ask him yourself.

343
00:16:16,240 --> 00:16:17,680
He's a hypocrite.

344
00:16:18,240 --> 00:16:19,000
I did.

345
00:16:19,480 --> 00:16:20,280
What did he say?

346
00:16:20,280 --> 00:16:21,870
Pretty much the same thing you just did.

347
00:16:21,880 --> 00:16:23,720
You and my brother had a fight?

348
00:16:26,880 --> 00:16:27,440
Tell me.

349
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:28,920
What happened between you two?

350
00:16:28,976 --> 00:16:30,288
Is it a difference in values

351
00:16:30,304 --> 00:16:32,240
or a conflict of interests?

352
00:16:32,240 --> 00:16:33,000
Yang Dezhi.

353
00:16:35,680 --> 00:16:36,920
I'm really sorry,

354
00:16:36,920 --> 00:16:37,640
Young Lady Zhao.

355
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:39,690
Why don't you tell me
why you two fell out?

356
00:16:39,700 --> 00:16:41,390
I'll write an article
and help you get even.

357
00:16:41,400 --> 00:16:42,080
Really?

358
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:52,720
Forget it.

359
00:16:53,680 --> 00:16:54,880
I'm not a cop.

360
00:16:54,928 --> 00:16:56,112
I'm not trying to get promoted.

361
00:16:56,560 --> 00:16:57,520
He's not worth my time.

362
00:16:57,720 --> 00:16:59,280
How can you let it go?

363
00:16:59,280 --> 00:17:00,784
You helped solve several cases.

364
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:01,648
Yuan Hong owes you.

365
00:17:01,650 --> 00:17:02,990
Not only did he not repay the favor,

366
00:17:03,024 --> 00:17:04,640
but he also gave you the cold shoulder.

367
00:17:04,656 --> 00:17:05,840
You have every right to be mad.

368
00:17:05,880 --> 00:17:06,880
I'm not a cop.

369
00:17:06,880 --> 00:17:08,120
What can I do?

370
00:17:12,120 --> 00:17:12,840
You could be.

371
00:17:17,640 --> 00:17:18,160
Father,

372
00:17:18,560 --> 00:17:19,440
didn't you notice?

373
00:17:19,440 --> 00:17:21,216
For a while there,
he was doing really well.

374
00:17:21,220 --> 00:17:23,190
He was busy all the time
and hardly ever came home,

375
00:17:23,200 --> 00:17:25,360
but he looked fulfilled.
There was a spark in his eyes.

376
00:17:25,600 --> 00:17:26,320
I think

377
00:17:26,320 --> 00:17:27,760
we should give him a chance

378
00:17:27,760 --> 00:17:28,680
to prove himself.

379
00:17:29,040 --> 00:17:30,200
The men of the Zhao family

380
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:31,200
aren't cowards.

381
00:17:37,320 --> 00:17:39,840
Following the police
to investigate cases

382
00:17:39,840 --> 00:17:41,120
is a lot better

383
00:17:41,120 --> 00:17:42,480
than having him loaf around all day.

384
00:18:03,260 --> 00:18:04,320
(No Entry)

385
00:18:04,352 --> 00:18:04,990
Take the picture.

386
00:18:05,040 --> 00:18:05,520
Here.

387
00:18:11,760 --> 00:18:12,960
Oh my.

388
00:18:12,960 --> 00:18:13,560
Look at that.

389
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:16,000
Uh...

390
00:18:33,680 --> 00:18:34,920
Young Master Zhao...

391
00:18:34,920 --> 00:18:35,920
Young Master Zhao's here.

392
00:18:55,500 --> 00:18:59,160
(End of Episode 9)

393
00:18:59,921 --> 00:19:01,561
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

394
00:19:01,561 --> 00:19:03,101
♪Troubled times
are but a laughing matter♪

395
00:19:03,101 --> 00:19:04,351
♪However, the world changes♪

396
00:19:04,351 --> 00:19:06,271
♪You'll still be by my side♪

397
00:19:06,271 --> 00:19:07,961
♪Side by side,
we journey through this life♪

398
00:19:07,961 --> 00:19:09,531
♪Praise and blame come and go♪

399
00:19:09,531 --> 00:19:11,101
♪If this is my final chapter♪

400
00:19:11,101 --> 00:19:13,601
♪I'll solve this mystery with you♪
